Description: Fix CVE-2026-44928 - EqualsUri ignores .absolutePath for URIs with a host set
 EqualsUri() previously compared the .absolutePath flag whenever the
 .scheme was empty, which is incorrect: for URIs that have a host set,
 .absolutePath is not meaningful (the path is implicitly absolute when a
 host is present). This caused EqualsUri to return URI_FALSE for URIs
 that should have been treated as equal.
 .
 Upstream replaces the (a->scheme.first == NULL) check with a
 HasHost(a) check (renamed from IsHostSet in newer releases). For
 uriparser 0.9.7 the helper is still named IsHostSet, so this backport
 calls IsHostSet directly.
 .
 The accompanying test cases from the upstream test commit are also
 included to validate the fix.
Origin: upstream, commit:723717c713a01c08efed6b3ded9583d7819e3386
Origin: upstream, commit:bd7f2e6c0c17dd78853f85107535391b4635a86d
Author: Sebastian Pipping <sebastian@pipping.org>
Last-Update: 2026-06-12

---
--- a/src/UriCompare.c
+++ b/src/UriCompare.c
@@ -81,8 +81,8 @@ UriBool URI_FUNC(EqualsUri)(const URI_TYPE(Uri) * a,
 		return URI_FALSE;
 	}
 
-	/* absolutePath */
-	if ((a->scheme.first == NULL)&& (a->absolutePath != b->absolutePath)) {
+	/* absolutePath -- not meaningful for URIs with a host set! */
+	if (!URI_FUNC(IsHostSet)(a) && (a->absolutePath != b->absolutePath)) {
 		return URI_FALSE;
 	}
 
--- a/test/test.cpp
+++ b/test/test.cpp
@@ -1965,6 +1965,76 @@ TEST(UriSuite, TestEquals) {
