Description: Fix CVE-2026-44927 ptrdiff_t-to-int truncation overflows
 Multiple uriparser functions truncated `ptrdiff_t` differences (the
 result of `range->afterLast - range->first` style expressions) to
 `int`, which on 64-bit systems can produce negative or wrapped lengths.
 Those lengths were then fed to `malloc(len * sizeof(URI_CHAR))` and
 `memcpy`, allowing crafted inputs to cause heap memory corruption or
 denial of service.
 .
 This is a backport for uriparser 0.9.7 of upstream pull request #304
 ("stop-truncating-ptrdiff-to-int") merged as
 dd98b0fa4ea69084ede319174ef107a5260d1334. The 0.9.7 source layout
 differs significantly from upstream main (older formatting, no
 CopyRange helper yet, smaller uriparse tool, different RANGE macro
 spelling), so the upstream changes were adapted to the same code
 paths in 0.9.7:
 .
   * src/UriCommon.c: RemoveDotSegmentsEx now reads the segment length
     via ptrdiff_t and rejects values outside [0, 3] before assigning
     to the int 'len' used in the switch, so an attacker-supplied
     huge-or-negative segment length cannot truncate to 1, 2 or 3.
   * src/UriQuery.c: ComposeQueryEngine guards the
     `*charsWritten = (int)(write - dest) + 1` cast against ptrdiff_t
     overflow. AppendQueryItem now computes keyLen / valueLen via
     ptrdiff_t and validates `(len + 1) * sizeof(URI_CHAR)` against
     `SIZE_MAX` before each malloc.
   * src/UriNormalize.c: LowercaseMalloc, FixPercentEncodingEngine,
     FixPercentEncodingMalloc, and MakeRangeOwner now use size_t and
     refuse lengths > SIZE_MAX / sizeof(URI_CHAR). MakeRangeOwner is
     the 0.9.7 equivalent of upstream's CopyRange.
   * src/UriFile.c: FilenameToUriString guards prefixLen and the
     Windows drive-letter charsToCopy against integer overflow.
   * src/UriRecompose.c: ToStringEngine pre-validates every
     UriTextRange (scheme, userInfo, hostText, ipFuture, portText,
     query, fragment, path segments) so the downstream
     `(int)(afterLast - first)` casts cannot truncate.
   * tool/uriparse.c: replace the RANGE() macro -- which truncated the
     ptrdiff_t length to int for printf("%.*s") -- with a dumpRange()
     helper that writes via fwrite() with size_t.
Origin: backport, https://github.com/uriparser/uriparser/pull/304
Author: Patch Platoon <security@root.io>
Last-Update: 2026-06-13

