Description: CVE-2026-42371 - Fix range-length truncation in CompareRange
 On 64-bit platforms the pointer-difference range lengths in
 uriCompareRange* were cast to int. Two URI text ranges that differed in
 length by 2^31 / 2^32 bytes could be treated as equal-length and then
 compared byte-by-byte, allowing an out-of-bounds read on crafted multi-
 gigabyte URI components (CVE-2026-42371, CWE-197 numeric truncation).
 .
 Use ptrdiff_t lengths and compare lengths before content; cast the
 length to size_t for URI_STRNCMP. Also add the upstream regression test
 (test/CompareRangeLengthWrap.cpp) and wire it into the testrunner build.
 .
 Backported from uriparser 1.0.1 (upstream commits 2b014fad and 47bab9f0).
 The hunks were regenerated against Debian's tab-indented 0.9.7+dfsg-2
 source so the patch applies cleanly without --ignore-whitespace.
